### About

Overview:

> Each year the European Community concludes a number of Agreements with third countries, as well as with international organisations.  These Agreements may be of an extensive nature, such as Trade, Cooperation and Development and Association Agreements or they may cover a wide range of specific subjects including: textiles; fisheries; customs; science and technology; transport; etc.

> Agreements with third countries or organisations may also be concluded by the European Union under the terms laid down in Articles 24 and 38 of the Treaty on European Union, for matters within the Common Foreign and Security Policy (CFSP) or Police and Judicial Cooperation in Criminal Matters.

> In addition, Conventions may be concluded between the Member States of the European Union in various fields, such as Company Law and Double Taxation (Article 293 of the Treaty establishing the European Community).

> Furthermore, Conventions between the Member States of the European Union may be established for adoption by them in matters concerning Police and Judicial Cooperation in Criminal Matters (Article 34 of the Treaty on European Union).

> Information concerning these Agreements and Conventions, including those in the process of being approved, can be obtained through this website.  This information will be up-dated daily and will include dates of signature, approval and entry into force.  Reference will also be made to any relevant reservations or declarations made by a Party to an Agreement or Convention and the texts of these declarations will be made available, in full, on this website.

### Data

Fields include:

  * Agreement details
    * Title
    * Signature (Date + Place)
    * Entry into force 	
    * J.O. Reference
    * Observations
  * Ratification Details 	
    * Party
    * Signature
    * Notification
    * Entry into force 
    * Decl/Res
    * Observations

### Downloading

No bulk download. 

Material can be viewed in a list by selecting the full range of years (1950-present) from the search interface:

 * <http://www.consilium.europa.eu/showPage.aspx?id=297&lang=en>
